<TITLE> No mercy for terror-tied AL MPs: Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 5 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has warned that not even MPs of her Awami League party will be spared if found involved with terrorist activities, tender manipulation and extortion. Awami League secretary general and local government minister Syed Ashraful Islam briefed the reporters after Awami League Parliamentary Party meeting on Thursday. The meeting was held at ruling party's conference room at parliament building with Hasina in the chair after the third session came to a close. AL president Hasina directed the party MPs to strengthen party operations in their constituencies. Ashraf quoted her as saying that those MP who will create chaos or fuel grouping in the party will be dealt with. The general secretary said the campaign for roping in new members was discussed and the campaign would be launched between late November and early December, Ashraf said He said, "We want to hold another council in three years." "So we want to arrange the council at all levels beginning from upazila levels after finishing member collection within two or three months," he said. bdnews
